<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-017-466  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 017 466.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>US Sage MainLan to have wider distribution. (local area network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   US Sage Inc. (contracts)Software Resource Group (contracts).andO;Product:   MainLAN (Network operating system) (usage).andO;Topic:     ContractsLocal Area NetworksDistribution AgreementsDistributorsSoftware Publishers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>US SAGE MAINLAN TO HAVE WIDER DISTRIBUTION LONGWOOD, FLORIDA, USA, 1989 DEC14 (NB) --  MainLan, US Sage's peer to peer local area network (LAN) will beavailable nationwide through the 13,000 dealers and VARs associated withdistributor Software Resource (San Rafael, CA).andM;US Sage and Software Resource have signed a new agreement to make thisdistribution arrangement possible.andP;  MainLan is aimed at the lower end of theLAN market, the end user who can benefit from a small, cost-efficient,&quot;shelf-explanatory&quot; LAN product.andM;US Sage introduced the product by marketing directly to end users.andP;  The newagreement is a step in the company's shift toward developing key marketingprograms with national distributors to make MainLan available to a much widermarket.andM;MainLan is a full featured LAN incorporating the network hardware functionson a single proprietary Local Area Network Communications Interface Adaptor(LANCIA) chip.andP;  It will run network versions of many of the most popularsoftware programs without additional software.andP;  The system does not require adedicated file server and is compatible with Novell NetWare.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19900103/Press Contact: Alex DuBrow, US Sage, 407-331-4400)</TEXT></DOC>